Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.38,0:01:14.97,Lyrics Top,,0,0,0,,Fly toward the galaxy, Gundam!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.38,0:01:14.97,Lyrics,,0,0,0,,Ginga e mukatte tobeyo GANDAMU
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.05,0:01:21.39,Lyrics Top,,0,0,0,,Mobile Suit Gundam! Gundam!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.05,0:01:21.39,Lyrics,,0,0,0,,Kidou senshi GANDAMU! GANDAMU!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.88,0:01:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The White Base made contact with\Nthe Zanzibar captained by Char...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.48,0:01:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,...but it was unable to shoot it down.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.23,0:01:54.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The most that the Gundam was able to do\Nwas defeat the mobile armor Bigro.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.02,0:02:02.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Breakthrough
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.34,0:02:11.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Could it be reinforcements?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.91,0:02:14.41,Default,,0,0,0,,There's another mobile suit approaching.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.41,0:02:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Where are the guys who hit the showers?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.46,0:02:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,On the decks, maintaining their machines.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.00,0:02:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,- Fraw Bow, launch one or two of them.\N- Who should we send out?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.05,0:02:24.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoever's in the best condition.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.97,0:02:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,- Hayato, then?\N- Tell him to hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.88,0:02:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Hayato, please head out in the Guntank.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.26,0:02:30.65,Default,,0,0,0,,All machines remain on standby.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.65,0:02:32.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll prepare the Guntank for a sortie.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.77,0:02:35.18,Default,,0,0,0,,- So it's just one enemy craft?\N- We're counting on you, Hayato!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.18,0:02:36.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.19,0:02:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}- You're only sending out the Guntank?\N- Mr. Kai's still In the shower room...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.80,0:02:43.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand. I've got a few ideas myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.81,0:02:46.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Have Hayato go on ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.92,0:02:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Amuro says he'll launch in the Gundam too.\NIs that all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.04,0:02:53.16,Default,,0,0,0,,That's fine. Let him launch.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.89,0:02:58.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Sayla. Why don't you lie down for a while.\NUse one of the rooms in the gravity block.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.79,0:03:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,But the enemy...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.30,0:03:03.67,Default,,0,0,0,,We've got Lieutenant Sleggar to cover you.\NGet some rest. That's an order.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.67,0:03:05.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes, sir.\NI'll do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.37,0:03:15.85,Default,,0,0,0,,What were the results of her medical exam?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.85,0:03:18.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing out of the ordinary.\NShe's in perfect health.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.52,0:03:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that so.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.13,0:03:25.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm proceeding on a direct course.\NContact with the enemy in 110 seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.49,0:03:27.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I'll cut radio communications.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.01,0:03:30.74,Default,,0,0,0,,That must be it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.42,0:03:39.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Wh-What's that mobile armor?\NIt's different from the last one.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.69,0:03:46.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So Dimitri took off?\NEven though I clearly warned him not to?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.05,0:03:49.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did you let him do it,\Nwithout my authorization?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.17,0:03:51.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry to say this, Captain Char...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.81,0:03:54.77,Default,,0,0,0,,...but you would have stopped him\Nfrom avenging Lieutenant Tokwan.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.08,0:04:00.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, Dimitri already has experience\Nas a test pilot for the mobile armor Zakrello.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.38,0:04:03.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I've never heard of such a mobile armor.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.95,0:04:06.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It was abandoned\Nbefore it could be properly tested.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.49,0:04:09.70,Default,,0,0,0,,But Dimitri said that\Nthe Zakrello's diffuse beam cannon...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.70,0:04:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you that this is our own backyard.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.24,0:04:15.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Right now, we can even contact\NDren's patrol fleet for assistance.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.23,0:04:17.38,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.38,0:04:20.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I know how you all respected Tokwan, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.09,0:04:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Dimitri must return as soon as he's satisfied.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.63,0:04:25.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir! Thank you very much, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.06,0:04:29.81,Default,,0,0,0,,If anything like this ever happens again\Nyou will be court-martialled, Lieutenant.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.16,0:04:35.65,Default,,0,0,0,,That's fast. It's different from the last one...?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.34,0:04:42.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It's loaded with missiles, too...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.80,0:04:47.83,Default,,0,0,0,,One more shot oughtta wipe out\Nthat mobile armor-wannabe!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.99,0:05:05.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Did I miss it...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.23,0:05:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't hit it! Hayato, just hang in there...!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.62,0:05:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Another mobile suit?! But it's awfully fast.\NWhat could possibly have such speed?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.82,0:05:21.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Here it comes!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.25,0:05:35.50,Default,,0,0,0,,This guy's annoying!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.90,0:05:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Fine, I'll take care of that clunker first!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.22,0:05:40.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Gotcha!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.49,0:05:43.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You fool. Same old move!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.50,0:05:57.78,Default,,0,0,0,,No mistake.\NI made a direct hit to his engine.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.84,0:06:05.37,Default,,0,0,0,,My computer predicted his moves easily.\NWhat was he trying to do anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.37,0:06:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Amuro? Do you read me?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.04,0:06:10.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Destruction of mobile armor confirmed.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.54,0:06:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}No enemy movements currently detected.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.88,0:06:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Roger. Two hits taken by Gundam.\NI'll return to the ship quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.29,0:06:32.71,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?\NDid two battles in a row tire you out?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.71,0:06:35.61,Default,,0,0,0,,No. Gundam's right arm was damaged, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.86,0:06:40.07,Default,,0,0,0,,But we've wiped out the immediate enemies.\NThere's no need to be so hasty.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.07,0:06:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You're only saying that because\Nyou don't know Char, Lieutenant.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.80,0:06:46.67,Default,,0,0,0,,He'll be after us soon with a new plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.68,0:06:51.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Every other word on the bridge is "Char".\NIs he really that special?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.64,0:06:53.65,Default,,0,0,0,,He thinks quickly on his feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.65,0:06:56.68,Default,,0,0,0,,He even pilots mobile suits himself.\NHe's incredible!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.68,0:06:59.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd love to meet this Char guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.82,0:07:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you need to get more rest?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.60,0:07:03.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm... fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.51,0:07:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Amuro, take a break.\NI'll look after things here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.87,0:07:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you. I'll head up to the bridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.38,0:07:16.36,Default,,0,0,0,,- Ms. Sayla...\N- Lieutenant! What about the main cannons?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.36,0:07:17.66,Default,,0,0,0,,No big deal!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.66,0:07:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Bright will yell at you. We're in combat.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.16,0:07:23.16,Default,,0,0,0,,- You're a pest, you know that?\N- Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.26,0:07:27.33,Default,,0,0,0,,- Let's talk again when things quiet down.\N- Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.52,0:07:31.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It's always about my brother, isn't it...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.75,0:07:47.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Can we contact the Camel fleet?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.81,0:07:50.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir! We're tracing its\Ncourse on the computer.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.90,0:07:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,- Open up a laser comm channel.\N- Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.96,0:07:56.25,Default,,0,0,0,,- Uh, Captain...\N- Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.25,0:07:59.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm very sorry about what happened\Nwith Dimitri earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.37,0:08:02.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Forget it. I couldn't care less\Nabout a weapon I wasn't even aware of.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.62,0:08:03.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Right...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.75,0:08:06.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll make it up to me one day, Mulligan.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.73,0:08:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.92,0:08:10.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It's Lieutenant Dren of the Camel fleet.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.11,0:08:12.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It's been awhile, Lt. Commander Char...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.97,0:08:16.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Or rather, it's Captain Char now, Isn't It.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.05,0:08:18.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}- You haven't changed a bit, Dren.\N- Sir.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.93,0:08:20.77,Default,,0,0,0,,We're pursuing the Trojan Horse.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.77,0:08:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,From where your ships are right now\Nyou should be able to interrupt them.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.64,0:08:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}You share a fateful bond\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.57,0:08:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Roger. Can you catch up with us?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.13,0:08:33.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Dren... have you forgotten\Nwhom you're talking to?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.97,0:08:36.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Forgive me, Captain.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.76,0:08:40.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Alter course, minus 110!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.31,0:08:43.75,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going after the Trojan Horse!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.31,0:09:20.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Artesia...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.47,0:09:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I can't ever forgive the Zabi family.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.92,0:09:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Please don't get In my way...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.45,0:09:43.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't approve of what you're doing, Casval.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.25,0:09:51.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So there are other sections of Gundam\Nthat are still severed?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.80,0:09:55.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Please replace the TC-17 block too.\NIt took a hit.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.29,0:09:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.72,0:09:59.12,Default,,0,0,0,,What's up?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.12,0:10:02.42,Default,,0,0,0,,- Can we talk for a bit?\N- Sure, no problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.19,0:10:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I was wondering... What do I have to do\Nto quickly become a good pilot?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.44,0:10:10.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I think you're already\Na good pilot, Ms. Sayla.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.43,0:10:12.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't flatter me, Amuro.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.66,0:10:15.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to survive, no matter what.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.71,0:10:17.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You're acting strange all of a sudden.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.49,0:10:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Even I'd like to stand a chance against Char.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.08,0:10:27.18,Default,,0,0,0,,No way! When he was using Zaku types\Neven I could fight him. But now he's...!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.18,0:10:29.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It was just an example, Amuro.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.76,0:10:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,If only I were like you...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.35,0:10:39.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Fraw Bow!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.42,0:10:41.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Just a minute. I'm confirming the data.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.84,0:10:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Three enemy vessels detected\Nat one o'clock, 30 degrees overhead.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.65,0:10:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,They appear to be Musai types.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.24,0:10:50.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Three Musai types detected!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.20,0:10:52.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Please go to battle stations!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.34,0:10:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The Zanzibar's behind us,\Nand the Musais before us.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.99,0:11:00.15,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to have to break through them.\NAll hands, level 1 battle stations!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.15,0:11:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Entering first combat speed.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.40,0:11:04.07,Default,,0,0,0,,All machine guns, check defenses!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.50,0:11:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,E.C. M. and laser searchers at maximum!\NDisperse combat level Minovsky particles!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.32,0:11:10.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Here we go again.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.99,0:11:14.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Level 1 battle stations!\NLet's go! Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.31,0:11:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Open machine gun turrets, main cannons,\Nmega particle cannons!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.70,0:11:45.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen well!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.91,0:11:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll use the same tactics as Captain Char.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.08,0:11:52.79,Default,,0,0,0,,We're sending six Rick Doms, Camel,\Nand Tokumel to attack the Trojan Horse!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.35,0:11:57.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I seem to have a fateful attraction to{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.25,0:11:59.55,Default,,0,0,0,,All craft full speed!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.69,0:12:21.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Mobile Suit Gundam
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.20,0:12:28.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Mobile Suit Gundam
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.96,0:12:31.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Our targets have passed the F line.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.14,0:12:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,They're Dom-type mobile suits.\NThe kind with skirts.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.87,0:12:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Fraw Bow! Send Lieutenant Sleggar\Nin the spare G-Fighter!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.02,0:12:39.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.47,0:12:43.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Lieutenant Sleggar! Please board\Nthe G-Fighter on Deck 2!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.34,0:12:46.76,Default,,0,0,0,,What a pain. Wasn't I supposed to be\Non the main cannons?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.26,0:12:49.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Hayato in the Guntank, heading out!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.66,0:12:52.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa! You're pumped,\NPetty Officer Hayato!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.52,0:12:54.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I'll join you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.80,0:13:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Please take note.\NDon't rely too much on this computer.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.64,0:13:07.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only accessible in G-Armor mode.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.64,0:13:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, the G-Fighter\Nis manually operated?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.72,0:13:11.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.71,0:13:13.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Suits me fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.33,0:13:15.09,Default,,0,0,0,,- Take care!\N- Sure thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.60,0:13:18.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Bright. Do you think\NLieutenant Sleggar will be okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.55,0:13:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The Guntank and Guncannon\Naren't suited for high-speed combat.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.82,0:13:24.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The more weapons we deploy, the better.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.66,0:13:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Reaching enemy in 90 seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.60,0:13:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The Musais are also closing\Nat maximum combat speed!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.46,0:13:34.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Sayla! Time to wake up...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.96,0:13:38.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Ms. Sayla's already on Deck 2.\NShe wants to launch.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.19,0:13:40.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. Is she alright?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.66,0:13:42.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you feeling okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.30,0:13:44.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm fine, Amuro.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.05,0:13:47.78,Default,,0,0,0,,They're not the mobile suits\Nfrom the Zanzibar, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.78,0:13:50.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm feeling a little out of sorts,\Nso I'll work it off with some action.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.75,0:13:52.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Sayla. You're acting strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.92,0:13:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Think so? I feel a lot better than I did earlier.\NDon't worry about me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.92,0:13:58.67,Default,,0,0,0,,- Be careful.\N- How impertinent.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.49,0:14:09.48,Default,,0,0,0,,- What's the Trojan Horse doing?\N- They seem to have detected the Musais.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.48,0:14:12.27,Default,,0,0,0,,They're increasing speed,\Nbut staying on course.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.83,0:14:16.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Nice move. They're trying\Nto break through the Musais.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.31,0:14:20.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Order the Camel fleet to concentrate\Nall of their fire on the Trojan Horse!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.07,0:14:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Will do.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.42,0:14:23.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Accelerate Zanzibar 10 percent.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.95,0:14:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Stay on course after the Trojan Horse.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.68,0:14:32.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Meanwhile...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.19,0:14:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,...having left Jaburo in South America...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.55,0:14:39.26,Default,,0,0,0,,...Admiral Tianem and his group of\Nthe Federation's Second Combined Fleet...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.26,0:14:41.14,Default,,0,0,0,,...were leaving Earth's atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.14,0:14:44.35,Default,,0,0,0,,They were setting a course for Luna II.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.67,0:14:57.82,Default,,0,0,0,,They're coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.82,0:15:02.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Now's my chance to proveet's see now...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.97,0:15:05.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.52,0:15:10.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that Mr. Sleggar?\NYou're jumping the gun!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.86,0:15:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,At times like these, he who rushes... loses.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.15,0:15:21.68,Default,,0,0,0,,They've split into two groups.\NIn that case...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.12,0:15:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, if Hayato's going left, I'll go...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.71,0:15:33.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are both Kai and Lt. Sleggar\Ndistancing themselves from the Guntank?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.80,0:15:38.16,Default,,0,0,0,,If we separate just like the enemy,\Nthere's no way we'll win.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.05,0:15:41.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm? Ms. Sayla?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.08,0:15:43.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Hayato, do you read me? We'll only win...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.37,0:15:45.25,Default,,0,0,0,,...if we coordinate with the others!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.25,0:15:47.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Those two think they can win on their own!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.08,0:15:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Roger that. Ms. Sayla and I will\Nmove in behind Kai and Sleggar!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.02,0:15:54.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.01,0:15:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.22,0:16:03.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Gotta lure him closer...!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.64,0:16:06.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.19,0:16:07.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Go!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.07,0:16:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.88,0:16:16.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Man! You sure are a lot calmer\Nthan I would've figured.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.42,0:16:17.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I misjudged you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.66,0:16:19.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait a sec!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.72,0:16:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh no!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.56,0:16:31.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Bastards!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.70,0:16:39.06,Default,,0,0,0,,They're good!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.91,0:16:47.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's the last one?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.63,0:16:58.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Fire at the area\Nwhere the Doms were destroyed!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.29,0:17:01.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Charge the Trojan Horse all at once!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.56,0:17:07.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Come in, White Base, do you read me?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.34,0:17:10.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Sayla here! We're heading back\Nto defend the White Base!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.95,0:17:17.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Please do! We need to get rid of the "skirts"\Nbefore we can start attacking the Musais.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.87,0:17:19.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So move it!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.16,0:17:23.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Block 6 has been hit!\NIt's the fourth hit!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.46,0:17:26.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The barrage is too weak!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.15,0:17:29.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The enemy's moving all around.\NTell them to just shoot without aiming.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.53,0:17:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Fraw Bow. Where's the Gundam?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.07,0:17:32.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Almost ready. Please wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.97,0:17:35.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The Musais have passed the F line\Nand fired beams!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.18,0:17:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll leave the evasive maneuvers to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.25,0:17:39.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.56,0:17:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Starboard!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.46,0:17:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Main cannons and mega particle cannons,\Nfire at the Musai's bridges or engines!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.56,0:17:51.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.53,0:18:00.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't just shoot blindly! Aim carefully!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.92,0:18:06.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Direct hit to the portside Musai!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.19,0:18:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Who told you to aim for their turrets?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.63,0:18:11.57,Default,,0,0,0,,If we destroyed the engine\Nthey couldn't use their beam cannons.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.57,0:18:13.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Concentrate your fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.47,0:18:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Direct all shots to the portside Musai!\NDon't even look at the others!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.31,0:18:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Sorry for the wait!or takeoff!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.84,0:18:26.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Hurry! The Musais are our targets.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.27,0:18:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Ignore the skirted mobile suits!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.44,0:18:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Roger that!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.08,0:18:39.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Here I go!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.29,0:18:42.90,Default,,0,0,0,,A skirted suit!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.94,0:19:06.51,Default,,0,0,0,,T-Tokumel!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.51,0:19:08.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Order the two Rick Doms to retreat!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.53,0:19:10.95,Default,,0,0,0,,They're in our line of fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.95,0:19:13.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Camel, Swamel,\Nwe'll destroy the Trojan Horse!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.77,0:19:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,We must take them out\Nbefore Captain Char arrives!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.27,0:19:21.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Two Musais... coming now!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.29,0:19:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Gunners! Aim at the portside Musai!\NForget about the one to starboard!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.06,0:19:39.04,Default,,0,0,0,,What's that?! I can't hear!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.04,0:19:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no sign of the Gundam!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.67,0:19:43.48,Default,,0,0,0,,- Whose Rick Dom is that?\N- It's Frasy's!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.48,0:19:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,He says he hasn't seen the Gundam.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.84,0:19:49.85,Default,,0,0,0,,That's crazy!\NThen where's it hiding?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.36,0:19:53.73,Default,,0,0,0,,- Did we get it?!\N- No! We hit one of their mobile suits!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.10,0:19:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,We almost have them!\NDon't let up fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.67,0:20:01.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}That's impossible!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.19,0:20:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The Gundam must be there. Where Is It?!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.88,0:20:05.91,Default,,0,0,0,,- Lieutenant Dren!\N- What now?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.08,0:20:08.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Something's approaching from bearing zero!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.41,0:20:11.66,Default,,0,0,0,,- What is it?!\N- It seems to be a mobile suit!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.66,0:20:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,- High-temperature object approaching!\N- A missile?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.83,0:20:17.13,Default,,0,0,0,,- It's not directed at us!\N- Swamel?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.69,0:20:20.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Swamel! Get out of the way!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.59,0:20:30.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I-It's the Gundam.\NThat white mobile suit...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.73,0:20:57.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the Gundam!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.98,0:21:03.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Above or below?!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.07,0:21:05.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Below!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.90,0:21:20.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Only the Musai is left!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.98,0:21:39.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Who would have thought that even Dren\Ncouldn't hold his own until I arrived?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.36,0:21:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The Trojan Horse's course?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.85,0:21:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,- Are you sure about that?\N- Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.22,0:21:48.27,Default,,0,0,0,,If we take a direct route to Luna II...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.27,0:21:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,...there's a 98 percent chance\Nwe're going to run into the Zanzibar.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.04,0:21:55.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Very well. We'll head for Side 6.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.21,0:21:56.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I concur, Lieutenant.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.86,0:22:00.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry I got the G-Fighter damaged...\NChief Petty Officer Amuro bawled me out.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.94,0:22:03.41,Default,,0,0,0,,You were in a hurry to score points, it seems.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.22,0:22:06.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.04,0:22:07.20,Default,,0,0,0,,But, Bright.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.20,0:22:10.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not really going to help us\Nif we head for Side 6...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.37,0:22:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,If we fought the Zanzibar in our condition...\Nwe'd have little chance of victory.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.80,0:22:16.01,Default,,0,0,0,,He's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.01,0:22:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It's obvious even from the outside\Nhow badly the White Base is damaged.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.68,0:22:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you foresee any problems, Mirai?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.76,0:22:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,No, not really... it's just...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.87,0:22:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Side 6 is a neutral Side.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.30,0:22:30.85,Default,,0,0,0,,The Antarctic Treaty prohibits\Nany kind of warfare there.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.85,0:22:33.48,Default,,0,0,0,,With luck, we can get the White Base repaired.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.08,0:22:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, it's also possible we'd\Nbe surrounded by Zeons.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.75,0:22:40.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't help that. We'll worry about it later.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.22,0:22:46.91,Default,,0,0,0,,What are the chances...?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.31,0:22:51.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Altering course.\NRedirecting the White Base to Side 6.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.73,0:22:54.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Side 6.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.94,0:22:57.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Of all the Sides that existed...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.13,0:23:00.39,Default,,0,0,0,,...it was the only one unaffiliated with\Nthe Principality of Zeon or the Federation...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.39,0:23:02.86,Default,,0,0,0,,...and not participating in the war.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.86,0:23:09.60,Default,,0,0,0,,All fighting is strictly prohibited\Nwithin Side 6 airspace.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.05,0:23:20.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Side 6, where reunions await.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.54,0:23:24.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Mirai with Cameron.\NAnd Amuro with his father.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.37,0:23:28.20,Default,,0,0,0,,In war, are people inevitably\Nforced to shed tears?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.20,0:23:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And then there is Conscon, who laughs...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.90,0:23:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,...and declares Char to be incompetent.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.14,0:23:37.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Mobile Suit Gundam. Next episode...\NFarewell in Side Six.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.78,0:23:40.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Will you be able to survive?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.35,0:23:44.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Farewell in Side Six
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.69,0:23:54.53,Lyrics Top,,0,0,0,,Amuro, do not look back
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.53,0:23:59.53,Lyrics Top,,0,0,0,,The star shining far off in space...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.53,0:24:09.75,Lyrics Top,,0,0,0,,Amuro, it's your homeland\Nwhere you were born
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.75,0:24:14.68,Lyrics Top,,0,0,0,,Do you remember the days\Nof your childhood?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.68,0:24:19.31,Lyrics Top,,0,0,0,,The morning when you woke up in warmth?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.31,0:24:24.69,Lyrics Top,,0,0,0,,Amuro, do not look back, Amuro...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.69,0:24:29.27,Lyrics Top,,0,0,0,,A man must hide his tears, hide his tears
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.27,0:24:39.58,Lyrics Top,,0,0,0,,Only look to tomorrow, to tomorrow\NForever...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.69,0:23:54.53,Lyrics,,0,0,0,,Amuro, Furimukanaide
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.53,0:23:59.53,Lyrics,,0,0,0,,Uchuu no kanata ni kagayaku hoshi ha
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.53,0:24:09.75,Lyrics,,0,0,0,,Amuro, Omae no umareta furusato da
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.75,0:24:14.68,Lyrics,,0,0,0,,Oboeteirukai, Shounen no hi no koto wo
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.68,0:24:19.31,Lyrics,,0,0,0,,Atatakai nukumori no nake de mezameta asa wo
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.31,0:24:24.69,Lyrics,,0,0,0,,Amuro, furimukanaide na, Amuro
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.69,0:24:29.27,Lyrics,,0,0,0,,Otoko ha namida wo misenu mono, Misenu mono
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.27,0:24:39.58,Lyrics,,0,0,0,,Tada ashita e to ashita e to, Eien ni...
